snippet.textDisplay:
I'm all for the guy wanting trial by combat. But please, no guns. It seems that we Muricans are getting so chickenshit these days that everytime anyone gets a little bit threatened, we pull out a gun and solve problems or confrontations by pulling a trigger.

Whatever happened to a good old fisticuffs? It's less likely to be lethal, and speaking from personal experience, there is something cathartic about being able to vent physically, and the struggle of it gets certain emotions out of your system. Most of the time, you get out of it a little beat up, but then you're calmer afterwards.

Seriously, it takes out tension. It's like blowing a load. These days people are so pent up but are too physically inept to do anything about it. And they pile on those emotions within themselves until it blows up in the form of a mass shooting. By all means, trial by combat.
